A coalition of civil society organisations under the auspices of Public Service for Good Governance (PSGG) has concluded plans to protest over what they described as underhand dealings in the Taraba State civil service. The coalition, in a statement signed by its convener, Comrade Peter Dasilva, noted that certain individuals in the Taraba State civil service had unduly enriched themselves and acquired humongous assets. Dasilva declared that the coalition was in procession of evidence of massive diversion of public funds in the state’s civil service. He said, “Our independent investigations have revealed that there was a massive diversion of public funds by some top government functionaries Taraba State, using various fraudulent means to acquire choice properties within and outside the state. “Documents at our disposal revealed shreds of evidence and means by which these properties were acquired which will be shared with various organisations in due course.” 